Brain Break #3 (Beach Party), Kids Fitness Workout, Exercise, Physical Education, DPA
Get your students moving with these easy to follow exercises!!  
4 Minutes
During this video, students are expected to follow the movement instructions that are shown on the screen. Each movement activity will last for 30 seconds before changing. The music in the video will motivate and inspire your students.  
Health and physical education offers students a unique opportunity for kinesthetic learning – they learn about healthy, active living primarily by “doing”, that is, through physical activity. In health and physical education, students discover the joy of movement, learn about their bodies, and develop physical and cognitive skills that will contribute to their lifelong health and well-being.

snippet.title: PE with Coach K- Would You Rather Be: Roblox's Edition
snippet.description:
Exercise gurus, students, and families will navigate through 9 rounds of questions on your favorite game in Roblox's.

Objective:
- You will have to choose the left and right pictures within 10 seconds.
- You will need to complete the exercise behind the picture for 30 seconds.
- There are no breaks at all during this exercise. This is 7 straight minutes of exercise.

This is a great activity for brain break, warm up/cool down, and to do multiple workouts.

ENJOY!!!!

What's Your Happi specializes in creating life-changing approaches that lead to fulfillment and happiness.

I'm Sandra LaFlamme eXp Realty.  When you join me at eXp Realty, you become part of a global family of agents and partners dedicated to transforming the real estate experience. Learn more about how I empower you and show you how to leverage our world-class education, strategic partnership and stock awards. 

Vernon struggled the first 20 years of his life trying to make sense of where he belonged and what he was going to do. Coming from an abusive and drug ridden household, Vernon was profoundly depressed, overweight with little self worth. He knew he wanted more, so he created the person you see and hear talking with you today. Starting with an understanding on being human, he learned from his grandmother and applied his educational background. From there he created a customized plan for each of the hundreds of individuals that he has coached with his system for success and happiness.

snippet.title: 🎃 HALLOWEEN DANCE PARTY 🎃 | Halloween Songs for Kids | Halloween SPOOKY Songs 👻
snippet.description:
🎃 HALLOWEEN DANCE PARTY 🎃 | Halloween Songs for Kids | Halloween SPOOKY Songs 👻

Halloween Dance Party by KRISTINA from KRISTINA'S WORLD OMG is a super fun, SCARY and also not – so – scary Halloween dance song for all young children and the young at heart to enjoy during this Halloween time of the year!  Kristina makes it SPOOKY and a bit CREEPY, but keeps the HALOOWEEN DANCE PARTY kid friendly where everyone, even the skeletons and witches, join in the FUN!

Halloween Dance Party is a great children’s Halloween song to celebrate the month of October and Halloween, but can also used as an October Brain Break activity anytime during the year.  The dance movements are all simple and easy to do, which really helps engage all children to participate, and keep the skeletons and witches busy too!

We made sure to make all of our characters Halloween friendly, but most importantly non-violent and not too scary for the little ones.

#halloweendancemusic #kidshalloween #kristinasworldomg

Please subscribe to Kristina - Kristina's World OMG https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHtt69gvD9Tb9dgWR0phnbg

snippet.title: Tapped
snippet.description: The high cost -- to both the environment and our health -- of bottled water is the subject of this documentary that enlists activists, environmentalists, community leaders and others to expose the dark side of the bottled water industry. Americans may rethink their obsession with bottled H20 when they learn of the unregulated industry's willingness to ignore environmental and health concerns, and the problems that arise as a result.

snippet.title: Circle Time - On the Farm Day 3 (There are many animals on a farm.)
snippet.description:
Welcome to Circle Time in Mrs. April's Classroom. I'm so excited to be aiding in the education of our young children through virtual/online learning.

Tune in weekdays for theme related circle time videos. Each video will be separated into two parts: 
(1) Circle Time Focus Board: We will be discussing the weather, letter/sound of the week, numbers/counting, color of the week, and shape of the week.
(2) Daily Message: We will read and discuss a daily message related to the week's theme

Today's lesson will focus on the information below:
Theme: On the Farm
Letter of the Week: Ff
Number/Counting: 4 (four)
Color of the Week: review (orange)
Shape of the Week: oval
Daily Message: There are many animals on a farm.
Word: farm animals

From the CD "#1 Best Kid's Songs!”
by The Learning Station®                                                               
℗©Monopoli/The Learning Station (All rights reserved.)
Copyright 1/1/2011

Lyrics and actions:

(Use both hands in a slow rowing motion.)
Row your boat, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Row your boat, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Shark mouth with thumb and pointer fingers.)
Baby shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Baby shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Shark mouth with hands connected at wrist.)
Momma shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Momma shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Shark mouth with forearms against forearms.)
Daddy shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Daddy shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Shark mouth with fists instead of fingers to look like no teeth.)
Grandma shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Grandma shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Same as daddy, but with fists instead of fingers to look like no teeth.)
Grandpa shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Grandpa shark, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(One hand on top of your head like a shark fin. Your other hand
rubbing your stomach with a hungry look on your face.)
Hungry sharks, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Hungry sharks, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Use both hands in a fast rowing motion.)
Row real fast, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo
Row real fast, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

(Hand wiping brow in downward motion.)
Safe at last, Doo doo doo doo doo doo doo doo

snippet.title: Incy Wincy & Igsy Bigsy Spider | Sing with Me | Songs for Kids | Brain Breaks
snippet.description:
Everyone knows Incy Wincy Spider, but did you know that he had a big brother with allergies? This new version of the classic tune is featured on our Cheeky Jams Album.

A perfect way to introduce and learn about allergies and how our environment can effect our systems. Don't forget to teach the children to SNEEZE INTO THEIR ELBOW OR TISSUE... Poor Igsy! A fun rhyme is to sneeze into your knees. You should try it :)

For babies, toddlers, preschool and kindergarten kids who are learning about the seasons, spiders and allergies and developing rhythm and co-ordination skills.

❤Jamaican Dance (Popular Dance Song for Kids)
❤If Animals Could Dance (Silly Action, Brain Break Song for Kids)
❤Button Factory (Brain Break, Movement & Math Song for Kids)
❤ Fooba Wooba John (Silly Action, Brain Break Song for Kids)

THE LEARNING STATION is a multi-award-winning children's group. With combined backgrounds and degrees in early childhood education, child development and music, this trio, has achieved international stature as leaders in the children's educational music industry. They presently have a collection of 35 award-winning audio and video releases and they have published over 400 children's songs that are part of educational curriculum's world-wide. They are widely recognized for their international hit song, "Tony Chestnut".
To learn more visit: http://learningstationmusic.com/index...

Jamaican Dance                                                                                                                                                                              From the CD, Action! Fun! Dance!
by The Learning Station
℗©Monopoli/The Learning Station 
(Sing words in italics and follow the directions for each dance movement.)
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh.
Come on everybody, girls and boys let’s smile and make some happy noise.
Let’s all sing our Jamaican song. Jump right in and swim, and sing along.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea! Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea!
Reach your arms up towards the island sun. Sway them like a palm tree, sing and
have fun.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea! Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea!
Shake your maracas like maracas shakers do.
Shimmy your shoulders and sing this happy tune.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea! Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea!
Shake your bodies up and shake your bodies down.
Keep shaking side to side to these very happy sounds.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea! Away, Away,
Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea!
Hands on your waist, move your knees out and in.
Keep moving them while we all sing.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea! Away, Away,
Away, Away, Oh. Oh, Yea!
Now, we all know the Jamaican song. Feel the heat
under your feet and let’s all sing along.
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Ouch! Away, Away, Ouch!
Away, Away, Oh, Ooh, that’s hot
Away, Away, Away, Away, Oh. Ouch, ooh, etc.
